    "\", p.332 10 Stepanova and Eriņš [20] Regulatory uncertainty \"The lack of legal framework and standards is another limitation frequently mentioned by DeFi users and developers.",
    "[…]In the case of DeFi, laws are replaced by a code that is normally developed by programmers not involving a wide range of regulators.",
    "\", p.332-333 11 Zetzsche, Arner [2] Regulatory uncertainty Network dispersion \"Enforcement becomes problematic in the context of DeFi.",
    "[…] How, in the world of DeFi, could a supervised entity enforce its oversight requirements visa-vis multiple, dispersed network participants that are spread around the world and subject to entirely different rules, ethics, and reputational concerns?",
    "\", p.187 11 Zetzsche, Arner [2] Automation This becomes obviously even more problematic if there is no tech firm in charge of the DeFi infrastructure at all, in those-so far very rare-instances in which technological systems become self-operating, whether intelligently (in the context of AI and its ultimate expression, the singularity) or through complete automation (arguably at the heart of the DeFi ideal)."
